** About the job **

At bdna, we exist to improve society. We choose to only work with clients that
have a direct impact on community wellbeing, safety and improvement - which
means that we get to make a difference every day!

The bdna Forensic team of business analysts, software developers, engineers,
testers and forensic subject matter experts work closely with law enforcement
and forensic laboratories to improve forensic service delivery through
specialist products.

** What you'll do **

Be a specialist in Cloud/Azure infrastructure. You will operate as part of the
DevOps team but collaborate across other internal teams. You will be
accountable for:

  * Cloud/Azure Infrastructure 
  * Design and Provisioning – gathering requirements and providing recommendations for the infrastructure required 
  * Security – ensuring that all active infrastructure complies with internal security policies and the constantly evolving industry security standards, e.g. ISM 
  * Performance – ensuring that all active infrastructure is performing at a level that meets our client obligations and expectations 
  * Optimisation and Configuration – constantly monitoring our active (and emerging) infrastructure to ensure that is optimised for performance and cost, as well as continuous improvement to ensure that we take advantage of new features and remain at the forefront of infrastructure technology 

** You will have experience that enables you to **

  * Design and implement our SaaS infrastructure 
  * Design, build, and optimise automation systems and procedures to maintain the platform and data, including the use of Infrastructure as Code 
  * Review and manage all environments maintaining availability, stability and performance in line with internal/external customer expectations 
  * Lead the implementation of security best practices in Azure, including identity and access management, network security, encryption and monitoring, in collaboration with security team. 
  * Ensure appropriate monitoring of terms of service, performance, capacity and security for compliance with expected standards to protect bdna and our customers from security risks, compliance concerns, and data breaches. 
  * Design and continuously review the use of features and licences to optimise costs 
  * Triage and resolve incident management and security compliance issues related to platforms and environments. 
  * Participate where appropriate in aspects of DevOps Engineering and promote industry standard methodologies in DevOps Engineering with a particular focus on security. 

** What you’ll get **

  * Work with a values driven team 
  * Learn from industry and capability specialists 
  * Collaboration and support 
  * Autonomy and ownership 
  * Flexible working arrangements 
  * Tools of the trade (of course!) 

** Education and Experience **

  * Degree in Information Technology/Computer Science or related field 
  * Microsoft Certified: Azure Administrator Associate (AZ-104) 
  * Microsoft Certified: Azure Security Engineer Associate (AZ-500) 
  * Microsoft Certified: Azure Network Engineer Associate (AZ-700) 
  * At least three years relevant experience 
  * Experience with Infrastructure as Code and Security as Code (Terraform) 
  * Azure Cloud Deployment experience 

** Work Eligibility **

  * Must be an Australian Citizen 
  * Must be located in Brisbane, Australia and permitted to work permanently with no restriction on work hours 
  * Must be eligible to be considered for NV1 security clearance. 

